            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I went digging a little bit into this issue\n\nThe error message doesn't originate from the C code ([`do_exedit()`](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/src/nvim/ex_docmd.c#L5919)) but from the fact that `edit` has the flag [`FILE1`](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/src/nvim/ex_cmds.lua#L845) in [ex_cmds.lua:845](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/src/nvim/ex_cmds.lua#L845)\nSo the function get short-circuited a lot earlier\n\nWould it be better to allow for multiple files in the Lua **and then** error later in `do_exedit()` ?\nOr can we do the erroring somewhere in the Lua ? (If so, not sure where)\n\nAlso took a look at https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/13009, but it doesn't feel right to change the error message\nCommands like `:exit`, `:cd` or `:find` also can error with `E77: Too many file names`, we wouldn't want them to suggest `:next` instead",
