        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> we can adjust the message to make sense\n\nSomething along the lines of `E77: Too many file names (glob(s) not supported here)` should be broad enough\nAlso is it still recommended to send a PR to [vim/vim](http://github.com/vim/vim) and pull it here as `vim-patch` ? (https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/13009#issuecomment-742707335)\n\n> Not sure why Lua is mentioned\n\nSince switching `FILE1` to `FILES` in [ex_cmds.lua:845](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/src/nvim/ex_cmds.lua#L845) disable the error message of `:edit *.js` and allow `do_exedit()` to be called, I figured there was some connection with Lua code\nMaybe not, I'm not an expert in multi-languages codebases\n\nBut just changing the message seems the better solution, I agree",
